### Description

In the WebGPU example, an array texture is given directly to the colorNode with the texture node. For this to work you have to add the depth value for the array and it works. 
However, I would like to pass the array texture to a shader in order to perform more complex operations and this apparently leads to type mismatches with the texture node. I took a look in nodes.js. I don't see a node for array textures and the node for 3D textures isn't the right one since array textures aren't 3D textures.

